Senegalese President Macky Sall has won re-election with 58 percent of votes cast in last Sunday's poll, election officials announced on Thursday, citing provisional results. The solid majority hands Sall a second term without the need for a second round of voting. Top opposition candidates are yet to accept the result. There are speculations that they could legally challenge Sall's win. Earlier in the week they had disputed unofficial results handing Sall a comfortable victory. More to come. ap/amp (AP, Reuters) Each evening at 1830 UTC, DW's editors send out a selection of the day's hard news and quality feature journalism. You can sign up to receive it directly here.